CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 25, 1961, pg. 16 reads: "Nurses' Installation - The first Nurses' Unit of St. Paul Baptist Church, was organized recently and installation services held on March 12, in St. Paul Church. The officers are, left to right: Mmes. Willie Mae Howard, secretary; Evelyn Coles, president; Sophia Collington, Alice G. Chapel, Louise Williams, vice presidents; Bernice Woodard, treasurer; Virginia Wright, program chairman; Ola Wells and the Rev. G.W. Coles, pastor, center. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of the first Nurses' Unit officers, from left: Willie Mae Howard, Evelyn Coles, Sophia Collington, Alice G. Chapel, Louise Williams, Bernice Woodard, Virginia Wright, and Ola Wells, posed with Rev. G.W. Coles, in St. Paul Baptist Church
